  "style": "APA",
  "texts": [
    "Baseline values of the dependent variable were controlled for in a two-level analysis of covariance modeling approach (Bodner & Bliese, 2018).",
    "Each model included all available data for each variable.",
    "Small variations in the sample size for each model reflected minor missingness among variables.",
    "All continuous predictors were grand-mean centered to aid interpretability; analyses were conducted in Mplus version 8 (Muthén & Muthén, 2017) using full-information maximum likelihood to address missing data.",
    "To maximize statistical power, main and moderated effects were modeled and analyzed separately (Bodner & Bliese, 2018)."
  ],
